[~decker] How can I remove deregistered NC's from the ClusterController.  In Nodes.java line #161 you mention using  
{code}
Topology.destroy( Components.lookup( NodeController.class ).lookup( unreportedNode.getName() ) );
{code}
but that you are wary of using this. It does fail anyway at line #420 of Topology.java
{code}
Topology.stop( config ).get( );
{code}
with the error:
{code}
java.util.NoSuchElementException: Failed to find cluster controller: ServiceConfiguration cluster arn:euca:eucalyptus:PARTI00:cluster:CC_71/ 10.111.1.71:8774:/axis2/services/EucalyptusCC:host-local:ENABLED
{code}
This is in a POC setup.

[~decker]  I added the code from the groovy script you sent me to Nodes.java.  The groovy script works and the Node is removed from the euca-decribe-service output. When I add the code to Nodes.java and deregister the node it does not work and the Node remains in the output in the NOTREADY state?  The IP being passed in is the same and there are no errors thrown? Another interesting thing is that if I unregister the node using the groovy script and then try an register it again it will not show up in the euca-decribe-service unless I restart the clc? What am I missing here? 
{code}
