[~decker] I added the code following code as well as the groovy destroy code (above)

{code}
nodeLog.append( "OLD:" ).append( nodeInfo.getName() ).append( ":" ).append( nodeInfo.getLastState() ).append( " " );
nodesToUpdate.add( nodeInfo )
{code}

The above does resolve the registration issue so that I can now register the node I removed with the groovy script. (Dan's Problem?).  However this still does not remove the node when called from euca_conf --deregister-node? Why does this work from the groovy scripts and not java?
